In a statement, President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama extend their best wishes to Muslims in the United States and around the world on the occasion of Eid-ul-Fitr. They highlight the significance of Eid ul-Fitr as the end of Ramadan, a month of fasting and prayer for Muslims worldwide. The President emphasizes the values that Muslims and people of all faiths share, such as charity, community, cooperation, and compassion. He also urges reflection on the importance of religious tolerance and acknowledges the positive role that religious communities, including Muslims, have played in American life. The President mentions the recent floods in Pakistan and encourages Americans to contribute to the Pakistan Relief Fund to support the relief, recovery, and reconstruction efforts. In conclusion, the Obamas congratulate Muslims on this blessed day and wish them Eid Mubarak.